UPDATE artist_info SET bio = 'Benjamin Thomas is a contemporary abstract artist based in London. His practice is an exploration of form and material, where each artwork marks a point in a connected and evolving body of work.

Thomas approaches painting as a means of releasing creative energies and intuition. Forms, gestures and surfaces carry from one piece to the next, reappearing through layering, reproduction and shifts in process. Earlier works often inform later ones, creating connections across different materials and formats. Each work stands independently, yet also contributes to a broader aesthetic — a thread that runs through the practice as textures and finish evolve.

His Upcycled series extends this approach to found objects: vinyl records are thrifted across East London, and given a second artistic life where paint and sound coexist within a single frame.';

